==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ligroin
<hw>Lig"ro*in</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g"r⟦osl⟧*⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A trade name applied somewhat indefinitely to some of the volatile
products obtained in refining crude petroleum. It is a complex and
variable mixture of several hydrocarbons, generally boils below 170⟦deg⟧
Fahr., and is more inflammable than safe kerosene. It is used as a
solvent, as a carburetant for air gas, and for illumination in special
lamps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

